history.content:
This reserved category filled up, however, I recommended waitlisting the class in Phase II if you are interested in taking it. If anyone from the specific category drops the next student on the waitlist who meets that criteria will be enrolled.

In addition, during the adjustment period all reserved categories will be released any open seats in the class will go to those on the waitlist.

<md>I'm currently a rising sophomore BioE major interested in enrolling in EECS 16A. I wish I had realized this interest earlier, but oh well.

According to the class schedule, there are 10 reserved seats for COE sophomores. However, this number only shows up in the bar graphic, but not under the section titled "Current enrollment." Given that my phase 2 start date is pretty early (July 19th at 2 PM), is there a good chance I could take one of these seats? Or have the reserved seats been depleted already?</md>
history.subject: EECS 16A reserved seats
